name: real_world_invalid_email_smtp_path_over_maximum
description: |
  This address is 255 ASCII octets, so enclosing it in SMTP path angle
  brackets requires 257 octets and exceeds the 256-octet forward-path limit by
  one. The local-part and each domain label remain individually in range,
  isolating the aggregate boundary.

  RFC 5321 section 4.5.3.1.3 sets the path limit:
  https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc5321.html#section-4.5.3.1.3
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
tags:
  - "real-world"
  - "email"
  - "email-address"
  - "smtp"
  - "invalid-email"
  - "invalid"
  - "length-limit"
  - "255-octets"
  - "boundary"
---
abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789ab@aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa.bbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbb.cccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccc
